{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix missing decode_fgs_service_accept implementation causing NAS decode failures\n\n### Summary\nThe function `decode_fgs_service_accept()` was referenced in the codebase but never implemented, causing segmentation faults when 5G Service Accept messages were received. This adds the missing implementation following the existing NAS message pattern.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/EMM/MSG/FGSServiceAccept.h`: New header file with message structure and function declarations\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/EMM/MSG/FGSServiceAccept.c`: New implementation file with encode/decode functions\n- Message structure includes mandatory header fields and presence mask for optional fields\n- Follows same pattern as other FGS message implementations like RegistrationAccept\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen UE receives a 5G Service Accept message (message type 0x4e) during service request procedure, the NAS decoder attempts to call `decode_fgs_service_accept()` which results in undefined behavior since the function doesn't exist. This causes immediate process termination or memory corruption depending on linking behavior.\n\nThe issue manifests as random crashes during initial registration or service request procedures when the network sends a Service Accept message back to the UE.\n"
}